		<item>
			<title>Chris Koczaja</title>
			<link>https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/chris-koczaja</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/chris-koczaja</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>Chris Koczaja serves as LightWave Solar’s President and CEO, leading the company in its pursuit to deliver quality solar power solutions across the residential, commercial, industrial, municipal and utility sectors. Chris holds a Bachelor of Science Degree in Mechanical Engineering from Purdue University and has over 20 years of engineering and management experience in the energy sector including Chief Operating Officer for PHG Energy, and engineering and sales positions with Caterpillar and Michelin. His work has included distributed energy development, novel waste to energy project design and construction, and process improvements, as well as achievement of Six Sigma Black Belt Certification. Chris serves on the board of Amicus Solar Cooperative and is President of the Tennessee Solar Energy Industries Association (TenneSEIA).</p>]]></description>
			<category>Team</category>
			<pubDate>Tue, 24 Jun 2025 10:18:19 -0500</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Carrie Horrocks</title>
			<link>https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/carrie-horrocks</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/carrie-horrocks</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>Carrie’s experience in the solar EPC space started in 2016 as Controller for a solar company in Atlanta, GA and transferred to LightWave in the summer of 2025. With a bachelor's from App State and a master's from Wake Forest, Carrie is a CPA who volunteers coaching youth soccer and basketball. She and her husband have three kids. Carrie served as Treasurer of the Georgia Solar Energy Association from 2019-2025 and currently serves on the board of the Amicus O&amp;M Cooperative.</p>]]></description>
			<category>Team</category>
			<pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 14:48:59 -0500</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>D.J. Rosebaugh</title>
			<link>https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/d-j-rosebaugh</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/d-j-rosebaugh</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>D.J. leads LightWave’s sales consultants and manages developer partnerships. D.J. holds a Bachelor of Science Degree in Industrial Technology from Eastern Illinois University, with post graduate work in business leadership. As an executive with 21 years of experience in the semiconductor industry, D.J. lead various roles in marketing, project management and strategy. Needing to become more aligned with his passion for clean energy and climate change, he changed to a career in solar energy. Since 2009 D.J. has led sales, operations, and management teams at residential, commercial, and industrial solar engineering &amp; installation companies based in Texas. D.J. moved from Texas to Tennessee and joined the LightWave in 2020.</p>]]></description>
			<category>Team</category>
			<pubDate>Tue, 24 Jun 2025 10:35:24 -0500</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>JP Plumlee</title>
			<link>https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/jp-plumlee</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/jp-plumlee</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>JP Plumlee first met LightWave Solar in 2007 when he helped install the first commercial solar project in Knoxville, Tennessee, at Mellow Mushroom. JP joined LightWave Solar full-time in 2011, and he currently develops solar PV projects for commercial, industrial and municipal clients. JP has worked in the renewable energy industry for over 15 years, holds a B.A. in Environmental Studies from the University of Tennessee and completed his NABCEP PV Technical Sales certification.</p>]]></description>
			<category>Team</category>
			<pubDate>Tue, 24 Jun 2025 10:20:18 -0500</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Nathan Baatz</title>
			<link>https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/nathan-baatz</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/nathan-baatz</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>Nathan Baatz joined LightWave in 2021 and has served as the Commercial &amp; Industrial Service Manager since 2023. He oversees maintenance operations across hundreds of residential, commercial, industrial, and utility-scale sites. Prior to his tenure at LightWave, Nathan built a strong foundation in biomedical equipment and industrial maintenance leadership—bringing valuable cross-industry experience to solar O&amp;M. He is a U.S. Army combat veteran with over 18 years of service. Nathan is dedicated to developing skilled technical teams and driving operational excellence across all facets of solar maintenance and safety.</p>]]></description>
			<category>Team</category>
			<pubDate>Mon, 15 Sep 2025 14:52:43 -0500</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Silas McRae</title>
			<link>https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/silas-mcrae</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/silas-mcrae</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>Silas McRae has been with LightWave since 2017 and has experience servicing and installing PV systems from .5kW- 2MW. Prior to working at LightWave, Silas worked for SolarCity as a Crew Lead gaining experience in installation and maintenance with over 400 jobs installed. Silas received a bachelors degree in Appropriate Technology from Appalachian State University focusing on solar, wind and hydro as well as receiving a certification in GIS. Silas is a Drone Pilot and holds active OSHA 30, NFPA70E, and CPR/First Aid certifications.</p>]]></description>
			<category>Team</category>
			<pubDate>Tue, 24 Jun 2025 10:33:12 -0500</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Evan Fitzgerald</title>
			<link>https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/evan-fitzgerald</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/evan-fitzgerald</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>Evan Fitzgerald has been working in the construction field for 10+ years including 8+ years in the renewable energy field and holds a NABCEP Certified PV Installation Professional. While in college Evan began installing solar, and he quickly saw that he wanted to make solar his career. After Graduation from MTSU in 2012 with a Bachelors in Commercial Construction Management, he joined the LightWave team in 2013 as an installer and is now a Project Manager. In his spare time he enjoys various outdoor activities and working on cars.</p>]]></description>
			<category>Team</category>
			<pubDate>Tue, 24 Jun 2025 10:21:21 -0500</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>John Robinson</title>
			<link>https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/john-robinson</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/john-robinson</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>John Robinson is LightWave’s Project Manager, making sure that our larger projects are set up for success prior to construction mobilization. Originally joining the LightWave team in 2011 as a Sales Intern, John has held various roles within the company in Sales and Operations since that time. John has a Masters of Science degree in Appropriate Technology and Environmental Design from Appalachian State University, where his concentrations were Renewable Energy and Building Science. When not at work, John enjoys relaxing with a good cup of coffee or beer, reading, seeing live music, and exploring the natural beauty to be found around middle TN with his wife Liz.</p>]]></description>
			<category>Team</category>
			<pubDate>Tue, 24 Jun 2025 10:34:59 -0500</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Jon Henderson</title>
			<link>https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/jon-henderson</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/jon-henderson</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>As Director of Field Service, Jon leads LightWave’s entire O&amp;M team maintaining large solar fields in various locations across the western United States. Originally from Bakerfield, CA he moved to Sweetwater, TN in 2020 and started here at LightWave that same year. Before LightWave, Jon worked in Inverter manufactures traveling the country since 2017. Jon takes pride in providing the best work environment for his team that way they can provide the best quality service to their customers. Outside of work, Jon spends his time with his wife and three children.</p>]]></description>
			<category>Team</category>
			<pubDate>Wed, 17 Sep 2025 13:34:31 -0500</pubDate>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Brandon Melber</title>
			<link>https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/brandon-melber</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.lightwavesolar.com/about/our-team/brandon-melber</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>Brandon is a 15-year active-duty Army veteran (currently with the Army Reserves) with five years of solar operations and maintenance experience, including residential service management, FLIR aerial thermography certification, and SUAS part 107 rating. He has been with Lightwave since 2022 and has been a great member of our team, using his skills and expertise as LightWave’s Residential Service Manager.</p>]]></description>
